item.title: Washington state under emergency as torrential rain triggers floods, mudslides and evacuations
item.description: Washington state is under a state of emergency from a barrage of torrential rain that’s sent rivers flowing over their banks, caused a mudslide to crash down on a highway and trapped people in floodwaters.
